<%= render 'shared/banner', title: "Welcome", cover_img: image_url("banner_img_2.jpeg") %>
<%= javascript_include_tag('shared/page_transitions.js') %>
<%= javascript_include_tag('shared/animations.js') %>
<div>
  <%#= render 'home/pc-animation' %>

  <div class="home">
    <div>
      <div class="home-block-section">
        <div class="testimonials-container">
          <p id="tag-line" class="lead-tag-line">
            "I'm a dedicated Full-Stack Engineer with over <%= years_experience %> years of industry experience, Makers Academy alumnus,
            and university graduate holding a BA in Digital Arts and Technology."
          </p>
          <div class="testimonials">
            <%= render 'home/carousel' %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <% #============================================== Languages =================================================== %>

    <div>
      <div class="home-block-section fade-in">
        <h3 style="text-align: center">
          Languages
        </h3>

        <div class="icons-container">
          <div class="icon-title">
            <h3>
              Proficient In
            </h3>
          </div>

          <div class="icons-block">
            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/ruby.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Ruby</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/javascript.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>JavaScript</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            A large portion of my industry experience has been in Ruby and Javascript, developing responsive JS
            interfaces and Rails applications. I also have knowledge working within front end frameworks such as React.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="icons-container">
          <div class="icon-title">
            <h3>
              Familiar With
            </h3>
          </div>

          <div class="icons-block">
            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/python.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Python</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/java.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Java</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/c-plusplus.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>C++</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            I'm familiar with several languages in and out of the commercial setting, and I'm continuously working to
            expand my vocabulary. I have experience using Python and Java commercially as well as C++ in personal
            Arduino projects and game development.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>


    <% #========================================= Frameworks/Libraries ============================================= %>

    <div>
      <div class="home-block-section fade-in">
        <h3 style="text-align: center">
          Technologies
        </h3>

        <div class="icons-container">
          <div class="icon-title">
            <h3>
              Proficient In
            </h3>
          </div>

          <div class="icons-block">
            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/ruby-on-rails.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Rails</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            My experience with Ruby on Rails spans more than 3 years and I'm well versed in the framework's
            inner workings. During my time at Amphora I was responsible for the development of several
            commercially launched Rails applications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="icons-container">
          <div class="icon-title">
            <h3>
              Familiar With
            </h3>
          </div>

          <div class="icons-block">

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/spring.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Spring MVC</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/flask.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Flask</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/react.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>React</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/docker.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>Docker</span>
            </div>

            <div class="icon-container">
              <div class="icon">
                <%= svg('dev-icons/nodejs.svg') %>
              </div>
              <span>NodeJS</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            My experience as a developer is broad and spans the entirety of the stacks I've worked on.
            I have experience in Docker, Spring MVC, Flask, Node, React amongst a plethera of other libraries and tools.
            It is my habit to constantly explore new tooling and I have a wonderful experience learning new things on
            the way.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <% #============================================== Experience ================================================== %>

    <div class="home-block-section fade-in">
      <h3 style="text-align: center">Experience</h3>
      <div class="organizations-block">
        <a href="https://www.amphora-research.com/">
          <%= image_tag('amphora-logo.png') %>
        </a>
        <h3>Software Engineer - 02/2021 - 05/2023</h3>
        <p>
          For more than two years I worked for Amphora Research Systems as a Full-Stack Software Engineer.
          I was responsible for devloping several commercially launched applications. My duties included maintenance,
          upgrades, front end UX design, testing and deployment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>


    <% #=========================================== Areas Of Interest ============================================== %>

    <div class="home-block-section fade-in" style="overflow: visible">
      <h3 style="text-align: center">My Areas Of Interest</h3>
      <div class="areas-of-interest-container">
        <div>
          <h3>Software Engineering</h3>
          <%= svg("graphic-01-coding.svg") %>
          <p>
            My primary skill set is in programming and I have studied it avidly since 2019. I independently taught
            myself OOP principles, attended Makers Academy and joined the industry in early 2021.
            I'm continually broadening my knowledge and in the past year I have successfully completed six
            online development courses totaling over 250 hours of lecture time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>CAD & CAM</h3>
          <%= svg("graphic-02-3d.svg") %>
          <p>
            With a degree heavily focused on 3D design, it was only natural for me to find myself drawn into the
            captivating world of 3D printing and parametric modeling. I cannot adequately express how empowering
            it has been to witness the accessibility of additive and subtractive manufacturing for everyday
            consumers. It has allowed me to delve into mechanical engineering and kinematics in a truly meaningful
            manner.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Electrical Engineering</h3>
          <%= svg("graphic-03-electric.svg") %>
          <p>
            In early 2020, my fascination with the potential uses of microcontrollers prompted me to dive into
            the world of electronics. This pursuit led me to dedicate my spare time to studying this field,
            with the ultimate aim of bridging my knowledge between software and hardware.
            I continue to immerse myself in this area, aspiring to reach a professional level where I can
            design custom PCBs from scratch.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
